^*Bhondo717:^*N OK, first the auction.  I had a couple of questions as to why I did not bid Stayman, since I had 4 hearts.  I could have, but I find with 4-3-3-3 hands, particularly when I have honors in all suits, it is often easier to play 3N than 4 of the major. Granted mary could have a doubleton somewhere, and we will therefore sometimes score an extra trick by a ruff in her hand, but remember 3N is one less trick than 4@H.  So my style is to just bid 3N with 4-3-3-3 hands, even with a 4 card major. However, if you choose to always bid Stayman, that would be fine as well.|
