^*Bhondo717:^*N Now, as to the play of the hand. After the opening lead is won in dummy, mary can assume bev has the K of diamonds. Therefore she can plan the hand out to take 9 tricks.  3 diamonds, 3 clubs (at least), and at least 3 tricks in the majors (2 aces and one of the Qs or Js.)  The easiest way to get 3 tricks in diamonds is to lead low towards the Q, rather than leading the ten of diamonds off dummy.  The way mary played diamonds she only got 2 diamond tricks.|
