^*Bhondo717:^*N So probably her best play is to play a low heart to the J thereby establishing 2 heart tricks for sure. If it wins, she can lead a low diamond towards the Q. if it loses, she can get to her hand with a heart next time, and play a diamond.  The more important point is to count your winners and losers at trick one, and plan a line of play. I cannot emphasize that enough. many less experienced players flounder a bit  before settling on a line of play.  But if you get in the habit of planning, you will be much more successful.|
