^*Bhondo717:^*N OK, I think we need discussion on the declarer play and defense here.  In a suit, leading K from KQxx is correct, as you are trying to establish a fast trick. anna  picked the correct suit but led the wrong card.  Your objective in a suit contract is to establish fast tricks for yourself, because your low cards are probably going to be trumped.  However, your objective in NT is to establish the low cards in your long suit.  If you decide to lead a suit with KQxx, and that is often a good lead, you should lead low.  You don't have to worry about losing a trick, because eventually you can score the K or the Q anyway, it will not be trumped.|
